missing.game.world.nodes

Class WorldTile

  • java.lang.Object
    • missing.game.world.nodes.WorldTile
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class WorldTile
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class represents a WorldTile within the Game. It is the internal data structure used within a WorldNode. Within a WorldTile, there are different types of Tiles, such as "Grass", "Sand" or "Water", which contain different characteristics.

      • removePlayerFromPile

        public void removePlayerFromPile()
        Removes the player from the pile. If the pile only has one item, it retrieves that item from the pile, reverts the pile object into an item. This method assumes that the current object field is an instance of Pile.

      • addPlayerToPile

        public void addPlayerToPile(Player player)
        Adds the player to the pile. If a pile is not created yet, the object field is converted into a pile and the player is inserted into the pile.

      • addObjectToPile

        public void addObjectToPile(WorldTile.TileObject item)
        Adds the given item to the pile. If a pile is not created yet, it creates the pile and then adds the passed item into the new pile.

      • convertPlayerToPile

        public void convertPlayerToPile(Player player)
        This method should be called whenever a player disconnects from the game. It turns the player into a pile of items.
